						               													<description>Questions that burn under the nails of each and every leftist: What did Marx mean by fetishism? Who was Rubinstein - Freud's pet name for his beloved, a pendulum often used in hypnotherapy, or rather a Soviet psychologist? Did the localists in the 19th century labor movement want their own independent party locality, was it about local autonomy or was it after all about a local united front?&amp;#10;With 62 question cards including answers, the time between demonstrations can be passed in no time and people will have fun doing it. Every shared flat will be able to collectively raise itself to a high level of knowledge. Suitable also for the beginning of studies and as a source of nasty questions for/to the professor or student.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this game you are confronted with questions about leftist theory. Play Radical Pursuit cooperative and correctly solve the question as collective or do it in a competitive mode, collecting as much of your correctly answered questions that no one else could answer to win the game. In competitive mode you sure could also team up... it's up to you, what you make out of this game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
